## Packaging and Publishing

1. Install build tools if you donâ€™t have them:

```bash
pip install build wheel twine
```

2. Build your SDK into a wheel:

```bash
python -m build
```

This generates a `dist/` folder containing:

- `my_sdk-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl` (wheel file)
- `my_sdk-0.1.0.tar.gz` (source archive)

3. Install the wheel locally to test:

```bash
pip install dist/my_sdk-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl
```

4. Publish to PyPI:

```bash
twine upload dist/*
```

5. Install from PyPI in another project:

```bash
pip install my-sdk
```

